main event: A sighting of 20-30 unidentified objects occurred over Butler, Missouri on the night of September 26, 1952.
interesting points: The objects appeared as a small cluster of stars and made three complete circles in the sky., The sighting lasted for a total of 3 minutes., The objects were observed moving from south to north and then heading east, disappearing into the clouds., Observations noted no discernable features or sound from the objects., The conclusion of the report suggested that the sightings may have been birds.
sighted object: 20-30 unidentified flying objects appearing as stars
